.TH "yield_to" 9 "yield_to" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
yield_to \- yield the current processor to another thread in your thread group, or accelerate that thread toward the processor it's on.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" yield_to
.BI "(struct task_struct *p "  ","
.BI "bool preempt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "p" 12
target task
.IP "preempt" 12
whether task preemption is allowed or not
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
It's the caller's job to ensure that the target task struct
can't go away on us before we can do any checks.
.SH "RETURN"
true (>0) if we indeed boosted the target task.
false (0) if we failed to boost the target.
-ESRCH if there's no task to yield to.
